Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe For allegedly selling her one-day-old baby for N300,000, the police have arraigned one Chineye Nwako before the Lagos State Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ikeja. Nwako was arraigned alongside the alleged buyer of the baby, Happiness Bini, on three counts of conspiracy, child trafficking and unlawful adoption. They pleaded not guilty to the charges. It was gathered that the defendants committed the offences on October 4, 2019, around 10pm on Oki Lane, Sari Iganmu area of the state. The prosecutor, Ezekiel Ayorinde, told the court that the arrest of the defendants was based on information received by the police that Bini was in possession of a baby suspected to have been stolen. [READ ALSO] N1tn constituency projects: Probe not a witch-hunt, says ICPC According to Ayorinde, the offences contravene sections 269, 276 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015 (revised). The Chief Magistrate, Mrs B. O. Osunsanmi, admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties each in like sum. She ordered that the sureties must be gainfully employed and show evidence of two years’ tax payment to the Lagos State Government and adjourned the case till February 3, 2020, for hearing. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 